Software Engineer Intern

Omnitech, Inc., a growing professional services company focused on technology, is currently seeking a Software Engineer – Intern. Interns at Omnitech work side by side with professional engineers and consultants in a learning based culture. Interns are challenged to research and present information to fellow engineers.
Most of the following description is what we look for in our fulltime engineers.
As an Omnitech Software Engineer, you will be using the latest programming tools and techniques for creating highly customized and complex applications. In our dynamic and exciting development environment you will be challenged daily.
This position requires a candidate with strong interpersonal and self-motivational skills in order to meet deadlines. You must be a fluent communicator with both fellow team members and company clients. You must be able to apply your analytical skills to deftly troubleshoot and resolve development issues as they arise. You must be able to adapt to varied environments, projects and roles on teams.

RESPONSIBILITIES:
• Take ownership of any step in the development process from design through maintenance as required;
• Develop software based on specifications provided by internal and external clients;
• Mentor team members, and constructively contribute to enhancing the technical knowledge of the development group, as a whole;
• Conduct proper client support related to all company projects, as requested;
• Work mostly on-site at Omnitech with possibility of off-site visits at client locations;
• Produce timely and accurate reports of work completed;
• Perform and communicate in a team environment.

REQUIREMENTS:
• Pursuing a Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Science, or related field;
• Desire to learn technologies like C#, .NET, SQL, HTML, JavaScript, CSS, jQuery;
• Excellent analytical and problem solving skills with the ability to think quickly and offer alternatives;
• Organized, goal-oriented, motivated self-starter who can work well in a team environment;
• Working knowledge of agile software development life-cycle.

ADDITIONAL SKILLS:
• Experience with HTML5, Silverlight, Mobile Device Development;
• Experience with Microsoft WPF, WCF, WF, LINQ;
• Experience using Microsoft SQL Server: Entity Framework, SSMS, DTS/SSIS;
• Experience with Architecture patterns such as MVC and MVVM;
• Experience with developing for SharePoint 2010, Orchard, WordPress, DotNetNuke, or Joomla;
• Programming background in a high-level programming language such as C, C++,Perl, or Java;
• Knowledge of SQL Server Reporting Services, Business Objects, or Crystal Reports (using overall product; building complex reports);
• Experience writing SQL and performing administration for other database platforms such as Oracle, PostgreSQL, MySQL, MS Access, etc.;
• Experience with data warehouse development;
• Experience with Quality Assurance and testing of web applications or software.

PERSONAL CHARACTERISTICS:
• Energetic, comfortable working in a fast-paced environment;
• Hard-working and motivated, able to take initiative and meet deadlines;
• Comfortable working in a diverse, team-based environment;
• Detail oriented, well-organized and excellent ability to multi-task;
• Excellent communication, presentation, and interpersonal skills, confident with customers and business partners;
• A hands-on attitude in a friendly work environment.

CONTEXTUAL BENEFITS:
• MSDN Premium and Azure licensing as Microsoft Gold Partner
• Opportunities for formal and informal training on new technologies
• Support for career and life goals and development
• Free soda, coffee and other ingestible fuel to keep you going
• On-site exercise room with equipment
• Company matching on the 401k plan
• Reimbursement for tuition and certification costs

Qualified candidates must be legally authorized to be employed in the United States on a full-time basis for any position. Omnitech will not sponsorship for employment visa status (e.g., H-1B or TN status) for this position.

If you are interested in being part of an exciting and growing company, please apply. If you have what it takes to support our organization, then send your resume and salary requirements via e-mail to Careers@Omnitech-inc.com EEO

Bayer is a global enterprise with core competencies in the Life Science fields of health care and agriculture. Its products and services are designed to benefit people and improve their quality of life. At Bayer you have the opportunity to be part of a culture where we value the passion of our employees to innovate and give them the power to change.
Software Engineering Intern

In Bayer’s Crop Science division, we shape agriculture through breakthrough innovation that helps to nourish our growing world, preserve natural resources and deliver better solutions for all farmers. Using the creative spark that comes from human ingenuity, we seek to deliver world-class innovation, set new standards in sustainability, and drive our digital transformation. Our products include high-performance seeds & traits, crop protection solutions, and digital farming tools.

YOUR TASKS AND RESPONSIBILITIES

The primary responsibilities of this role, Software Engineering Intern, are to:
Work with stakeholders from various business units to identify high value opportunities where virtual or augmented reality can make an appreciable difference to the business;
Develop custom applications to address business needs and solve challenges including environment creation, object design and creation, texturing, substance design, UX, coding and scripting;
Be an advocate for these technologies and always focus on showing business value;
Maintain software development best practices including testing, version control, secure coding practices, etc.;
Partner with other teams developing Virtual Reality/Aumented Reality(VR/AR) projects to guide their efforts and bring cohesion to Bayer Crop Science’s overall VR/AR
strategy.
WHO YOU ARE

Your success will be driven by your demonstration of our LIFE values. More specifically related to this position, Bayer seeks an incumbent who possesses the following:

Required Qualifications:
Currently enrolled in a Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, STEM or Arts degree with emphasis on virtual technologies;
Experience or knowledge of building 3D environments, games and/or experiences with Unity and Unreal Engine;
Experience or knowledge of 3D modeling using tools such as Blender, 3ds Max and MODO;
C# experience;
Experience or knowledge of designing core game mechanics/interactions;
Experience or knowledge of Visual Studio and GitHub.
Preferred Qualifications:
Experience in materials rendering and substance tools;
Experience within the agriculture field;
Experience with UI/UX best practices.
YOUR APPLICATION
Bayer offers a wide variety of competitive compensation and benefits programs. If you meet the requirements of this unique opportunity, and you have the "Passion to Innovate" and the "Power to Change", we encourage you to apply now. To all recruitment agencies: Bayer does not accept unsolicited third party resumes.
